TY  - JOUR
AU  - Vaarmets, Tarvo
AU  - Liivamägi, Kristjan
AU  - Talpsepp, Tõnn
T1  - How Does Learning and Education Help to Overcome the Disposition Effect?*
PY  - 2019
Y1  - 2019/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfy006
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
SP  - 801
EP  - 830
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - The paper assesses how intelligence, education, and learning affect the disposition effect using our exhaustive NASDAQ OMX Tallinn dataset. We employ survival analysis to show that higher intelligence and stronger learning abilities as measured by education level and the type of education lessen the disposition effect. More highly educated and intelligent investors also learn faster by trading. We find that mathematical abilities are beneficial for overcoming the disposition effect and propose that learning ability is one of the most important components of intelligence in affecting the disposition effect.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfy006
ER  - 



